main event: A dark, solid object with a definite shape was sighted over Colorado in 1967.
interesting points: The object was cloudy, but appeared to be illuminated from within.
The object was seen for less than 30 seconds.
The object was still in sight when the observation terminated.
The report mentions contacting various organizations about potential balloon sightings in the area around the same time, but none of them could account for the object.
The report concludes that the cause of the sighting is unknown.
sighted object: a dark, solid object with a definite shape
photographs: yes, the report indicates photographs were taken
